
1. findElement() is a method in the WebDriver Interface in Selenium. It is used to locate the first 
element that matches the specified locator strategy and conditions. 
2. It's return type is WebElement.
3. When using the @find element command in Selenium and no matching element is found on the page,
the exception thrown is called "NoSuchElementException". 


ex - WebElement sbmtBtn = driver.findElement(By.id("Btn")).click();